00:20:17,665 --> 00:20:19,385
You want to go home?

286
00:20:19,465 --> 00:20:21,665
You asked me out.

287
00:20:22,945 --> 00:20:25,264
Why did we have to come here?

288
00:20:25,345 --> 00:20:26,744
How is it romantic?

289
00:20:29,744 --> 00:20:31,065
I don't know.

290
00:20:31,145 --> 00:20:32,465
I wanted to come.

291
00:20:33,185 --> 00:20:34,625
Did you not want to come?

292
00:20:36,065 --> 00:20:38,065
Do I look like I wanted to come?

293
00:20:52,185 --> 00:20:53,984
Where should we go for our date?

294
00:20:54,065 --> 00:20:57,465
The market is good enough for you.

295
00:20:58,145 --> 00:21:00,065
Give me somewhere more meaningful.

296
00:21:02,305 --> 00:21:03,305
Does anyone know

297
00:21:03,865 --> 00:21:04,945
where Nut wants to go?

298
00:21:05,425 --> 00:21:07,305
Yes, I know a place.

299
00:21:07,385 --> 00:21:10,705
Nut wrote how he wanted to go there
and drew a picture of it long ago.

300
00:21:12,585 --> 00:21:13,585
Where is it?

301
00:21:15,585 --> 00:21:16,784
Follow me, Nut.

302
00:21:16,865 --> 00:21:17,825
Where are you going?

303
00:21:19,345 --> 00:21:21,024
Answer me first, Tofu.

304
00:21:22,065 --> 00:21:23,105
Tofu.

305
00:21:24,345 --> 00:21:26,024
What made you think I wanted to come?

306
00:21:33,465 --> 00:21:34,744
Does it matter?

307
00:21:36,264 --> 00:21:38,185
I just want you to be happy,

308
00:21:39,465 --> 00:21:40,705
smile

309
00:21:41,185 --> 00:21:43,425
and laugh like you did today.

310
00:21:44,784 --> 00:21:47,705
You need to remember
this moment to write the script.

311
00:21:49,105 --> 00:21:50,825
I like seeing you happy.

312
00:22:05,665 --> 00:22:07,465
Tofu.

313
00:22:07,544 --> 00:22:09,065
Let's find a place to hide.

314
00:22:10,385 --> 00:22:11,825
Why?

315
00:22:11,905 --> 00:22:13,465
I've never played in the rain.

316
00:22:14,145 --> 00:22:15,784
Woo-hoo.

317
00:22:15,865 --> 00:22:17,585
You've gone crazy.

318
00:22:17,665 --> 00:22:19,225
Let's go or you'll get sick.

319
00:22:19,305 --> 00:22:21,225
The rain is so cooling, Nut.

320
00:22:21,825 --> 00:22:23,585
It's as cooling as a shower.

321
00:22:29,705 --> 00:22:31,185
You will be dry later

322
00:22:31,744 --> 00:22:33,225
when the rain stops.

323
00:22:33,305 --> 00:22:34,504
Don't be scared.

324
00:22:35,504 --> 00:22:36,905
Come.

325
00:23:07,544 --> 00:23:08,945
Are you happy, Nut?

326
00:23:12,385 --> 00:23:13,345
Woo-hoo!

327
00:24:16,585 --> 00:24:17,945
I made coffee for you.

328
00:24:22,625 --> 00:24:23,744
You haven't showered.

329
00:24:25,984 --> 00:24:27,345
I'll help you.

330
00:24:43,865 --> 00:24:44,945
Do you know

331
00:24:45,784 --> 00:24:47,345
how things will end

332
00:24:48,225 --> 00:24:49,425
if you're too good to me?

333
00:24:56,024 --> 00:24:57,105
What did you say?

334
00:25:02,504 --> 00:25:03,385
I said,

335
00:25:04,185 --> 00:25:06,065
do you know how things will end

336
00:25:08,385 --> 00:25:09,345
if you're too good?

337
00:25:18,945 --> 00:25:19,825
I'm kidding.

338
00:25:20,625 --> 00:25:22,225
Go away. I need to work.

339
00:25:25,744 --> 00:25:26,865
Go.

340
00:25:30,544 --> 00:25:31,705
Go take a shower.

341
00:26:12,105 --> 00:26:13,264
What's wrong with me?

342
00:26:14,304 --> 00:26:15,665
Is it because of Nut?

343
00:26:18,264 --> 00:26:20,024
My heart is racing

344
00:26:21,345 --> 00:26:22,544
and my face

345
00:26:23,425 --> 00:26:25,024
feels hot.

346
00:26:32,585 --> 00:26:33,984
It's hotter than usual.

347
00:26:39,865 --> 00:26:41,304
Why is my body so hot?

348
00:26:43,024 --> 00:26:44,385
My whole body feels hot.

349
00:26:45,705 --> 00:26:47,225
But I'm happy.

350
00:26:48,744 --> 00:26:49,905
Is this

351
00:26:50,945 --> 00:26:52,105
what they call…

352
00:27:44,264 --> 00:27:46,705
This is for you.

353
00:27:50,665 --> 00:27:51,784
Tofu.

354
00:27:56,865 --> 00:27:57,945
Tofu.

355
00:28:02,465 --> 00:28:04,065
You are so gross.

356
00:28:05,065 --> 00:28:06,304
Go take a shower.

357
00:28:08,784 --> 00:28:09,744
Tofu.

358
00:28:14,784 --> 00:28:15,625
Oh, my god.

359
00:28:17,024 --> 00:28:18,465
You're burning up.

360
00:29:13,264 --> 00:29:14,784
It ends with me caring for you.

361
00:29:47,865 --> 00:29:49,064
Look.

362
00:29:50,865 --> 00:29:53,665
-You're mine.
-Wow.

363
00:29:54,744 --> 00:29:56,625
-How was that?
-You're good, Nut.

364
00:29:58,105 --> 00:29:59,544
Watch me.

365
00:29:59,625 --> 00:30:01,145
Oh, no.

366
00:30:02,225 --> 00:30:03,225
Nut.

367
00:30:03,304 --> 00:30:04,465
You go first.

368
00:30:04,544 --> 00:30:05,544
BALLOON POP

369
00:30:06,945 --> 00:30:08,105
Watch me.

370
00:30:08,705 --> 00:30:09,744
Yes.

371
00:30:12,185 --> 00:30:13,825
-Oh, my god. Watch me.
-Oh, no. Nut.

372
00:30:14,425 --> 00:30:15,544
Oh, what?

373
00:30:17,304 --> 00:30:18,825
-Oh, god.
-Oh, god.

374
00:30:19,504 --> 00:30:21,105
Come on.

375
00:30:21,185 --> 00:30:22,064
I have to win.

376
00:30:23,225 --> 00:30:25,425
So close, Tofu.

377
00:30:25,504 --> 00:30:26,345
Go.

378
00:30:27,425 --> 00:30:28,345
Tofu.

379
00:30:28,945 --> 00:30:30,225
Let's go.

380
00:30:30,304 --> 00:30:31,145
What the hell?

381
00:30:38,264 --> 00:30:39,145
It's hard.

382
00:30:41,024 --> 00:30:42,825
Tofu, throw it.

383
00:30:43,984 --> 00:30:45,024
What's wrong?

384
00:30:47,264 --> 00:30:48,705
If I throw this ring,

385
00:30:49,585 --> 00:30:50,825
I won't have one for you.

386
00:30:52,145 --> 00:30:53,385
How lame.

387
00:30:54,024 --> 00:30:54,945
Nut.

388
00:30:55,465 --> 00:30:57,705
If you want me to propose,
buy me more rings.

389
00:31:00,544 --> 00:31:01,385
Nut.

390
00:31:03,225 --> 00:31:04,345
Thank you.

391
00:31:05,905 --> 00:31:07,264
Yours is bigger.

392
00:31:08,385 --> 00:31:09,665
Do you like this place?

393
00:31:10,264 --> 00:31:13,705
That's great. I'm happy
to take you to a better place.

394
00:31:15,145 --> 00:31:17,064
You make it sound like I'm dead.

395
00:31:17,625 --> 00:31:19,544
How do you know my likes and dislikes?

396
00:31:20,865 --> 00:31:22,865
I always pay attention to you.

397
00:31:25,504 --> 00:31:26,744
Let's take a selfie.

398
00:31:27,385 --> 00:31:30,064
I want to capture our day together

399
00:31:30,705 --> 00:31:32,264
to remember it by.

400
00:31:50,425 --> 00:31:51,544
Nut, look.

401
00:31:58,824 --> 00:31:59,984
You can see the candy.

402
00:32:08,705 --> 00:32:09,945
No.

403
00:32:10,585 --> 00:32:12,264
That trick is getting old.

404
00:32:14,585 --> 00:32:15,544
Tofu.

405
00:32:16,225 --> 00:32:17,504
Where are you going?

406
00:32:17,585 --> 00:32:18,945
I'm going behind the hut.

407
00:32:33,865 --> 00:32:34,865
Thank you.

408
00:33:30,865 --> 00:33:33,225
You're frying pork in the office?

409
00:33:33,984 --> 00:33:36,264
I can do anything for love.

410
00:33:36,345 --> 00:33:38,544
I worked on the recipe all night.

411
00:33:38,625 --> 00:33:40,345
Juea approved it.

412
00:33:42,264 --> 00:33:43,705
I hope he doesn't get cancer.

413
00:33:46,185 --> 00:33:47,504
The pork is way too burnt

414
00:33:47,585 --> 00:33:48,945
to eat.

415
00:33:49,024 --> 00:33:51,024
Nut eats it like this.

416
00:33:54,345 --> 00:33:55,705
Do you think he eats it

417
00:33:55,784 --> 00:33:57,304
because it's burned?

418
00:33:58,345 --> 00:34:00,425
It's about the person who makes it.

419
00:34:03,625 --> 00:34:05,105
If he were to fall for you,

420
00:34:05,185 --> 00:34:06,905
this pork wouldn't be the reason.

421
00:34:07,544 --> 00:34:09,025
He would love you for you.

422
00:34:09,585 --> 00:34:10,585
Do you understand?

423
00:34:13,025 --> 00:34:14,665
Who made it for him?

424
00:34:15,225 --> 00:34:18,264
Only his mom and Tofu live with him.

425
00:34:20,344 --> 00:34:21,904
Do you think that person…

426
00:34:23,065 --> 00:34:23,944
What?

427
00:34:39,344 --> 00:34:40,944
Don't be sad. I'm here.

428
00:34:43,505 --> 00:34:45,185
I knew you would come,

429
00:34:45,264 --> 00:34:47,225
so I waited for you.

430
00:34:48,025 --> 00:34:50,904
Thank you for watching me all night

431
00:34:50,985 --> 00:34:52,264
and taking me home.

432
00:35:27,025 --> 00:35:29,585
I'm taking responsibility
for giving you diarrhea.

433
00:35:33,465 --> 00:35:34,625
Did you tell your dad?

434
00:35:40,265 --> 00:35:41,665
He's busy.

435
00:35:41,745 --> 00:35:42,585
He'll just worry.

436
00:35:45,065 --> 00:35:46,465
If he worries,

437
00:35:46,545 --> 00:35:48,065
take good care of yourself.

438
00:35:49,785 --> 00:35:51,745
My parent isn't a doctor like yours.

439
00:35:52,625 --> 00:35:54,145
I don't take good care of myself.

440
00:35:59,665 --> 00:36:01,825
I'm looking for someone
to take care of me.

441
00:36:04,985 --> 00:36:06,225
I'm here, am I not?

442
00:36:08,625 --> 00:36:09,505
What is it, mister?

443
00:36:11,384 --> 00:36:12,745
I…

444
00:36:12,825 --> 00:36:13,825
washed them for you.

445
00:36:19,384 --> 00:36:20,585
Wait.

446
00:36:20,665 --> 00:36:22,145
Are you opening up to me?

447
00:36:23,985 --> 00:36:24,825
Opening up?

448
00:36:26,025 --> 00:36:27,265
What are you talking about?

449
00:36:27,904 --> 00:36:28,985
I'm just afraid

450
00:36:29,065 --> 00:36:30,225
the series will go under

451
00:36:31,265 --> 00:36:32,545
if you die.

452
00:36:33,225 --> 00:36:34,384
That's all.

453
00:36:37,145 --> 00:36:38,505
I won't die easily

454
00:36:39,424 --> 00:36:40,384
because

455
00:36:41,105 --> 00:36:42,985
-I will stay alive to hug you.
-Hey.

456
00:36:43,065 --> 00:36:44,705
Song, what are you doing?

457
00:36:44,785 --> 00:36:45,665
Song.

458
00:36:46,265 --> 00:36:47,985
-I love you, mister.
-Song.

459
00:36:48,065 --> 00:36:49,384
What's your problem?

460
00:36:49,465 --> 00:36:50,345
-Oh my.
-Let me go.

461
00:36:50,424 --> 00:36:52,265
-My god.
-What are you doing?

462
00:36:53,785 --> 00:36:55,305
Dad. Mom.

463
00:36:58,625 --> 00:36:59,464
Why are you here?

464
00:37:05,225 --> 00:37:07,384
We came to visit him.

465
00:37:07,464 --> 00:37:09,305
The doctor approved his discharge.

466
00:37:09,384 --> 00:37:12,145
He must have gotten a great caretaker.

467
00:37:12,705 --> 00:37:14,105
Mom.

468
00:37:14,185 --> 00:37:17,625
Be careful of what you eat next time.

469
00:37:18,464 --> 00:37:19,464
Yes.

470
00:37:19,545 --> 00:37:22,345
-Thank you guys so much
-You're welcome.

471
00:37:22,424 --> 00:37:24,705
-for taking care of me last night.
-Sure.

472
00:37:24,785 --> 00:37:27,345
You look better in real life.

473
00:37:29,464 --> 00:37:31,785
I was the one who accepted
your friend request.

474
00:37:31,864 --> 00:37:33,345
He was playing hard to get.

475
00:37:34,305 --> 00:37:35,185
Dad!

476
00:37:35,265 --> 00:37:37,825
You're being way too loud.

477
00:37:37,904 --> 00:37:39,625
People will think I've died.

478
00:37:39,705 --> 00:37:40,944
What?

479
00:37:41,025 --> 00:37:42,265
If you don't like yelling.

480
00:37:42,345 --> 00:37:43,625
you should leave.

481
00:37:43,705 --> 00:37:45,225
I'm going to drop him off

482
00:37:45,305 --> 00:37:46,825
and go to work.

483
00:37:48,025 --> 00:37:49,065
Go already.

484
00:37:49,625 --> 00:37:50,625
Let's go.

485
00:37:51,345 --> 00:37:53,985
Gosh, judging from what
you were doing on the bed,

486
00:37:54,065 --> 00:37:55,864
he's definitely more than a friend.

487
00:37:59,665 --> 00:38:00,864
Mom.

488
00:38:01,464 --> 00:38:02,904
This kid gets on my nerves.

489
00:38:03,545 --> 00:38:04,745
Be glad I'm your friend.

490
00:38:05,424 --> 00:38:08,825
Not every kid is like that.

491
00:38:08,904 --> 00:38:11,665
There are many good kids out there.

492
00:38:16,864 --> 00:38:17,785
Come on.

493
00:38:18,864 --> 00:38:20,105
-What?
-Let's go.

494
00:38:20,185 --> 00:38:21,185
Look at him.

495
00:38:21,665 --> 00:38:24,944
Who did he get his stubbornness from?

496
00:38:25,025 --> 00:38:27,065
You, I guess.

497
00:38:27,145 --> 00:38:29,464
-Really? Not from you?
-No.

498
00:39:56,944 --> 00:39:57,864
I'm sorry.

499
00:39:58,864 --> 00:40:00,065
I didn't mean to wake you.

500
00:40:10,025 --> 00:40:10,904
The thing is

501
00:40:11,665 --> 00:40:13,025
you had a fever last night,

502
00:40:14,665 --> 00:40:15,904
so I wiped your body down.

503
00:40:18,384 --> 00:40:19,505
You said you were cold

504
00:40:21,384 --> 00:40:22,225
so I…

505
00:40:26,065 --> 00:40:27,145
Thank you.

506
00:40:28,625 --> 00:40:30,225
It got much warmer

507
00:40:31,065 --> 00:40:32,185
with you next to me.

508
00:42:05,464 --> 00:42:07,745
Having fever for the first time sucks.

509
00:42:11,265 --> 00:42:12,625
But I got a lot better…

510
00:42:15,065 --> 00:42:16,265
when you hugged me.

511
00:42:18,985 --> 00:42:21,345
Human bodies work in a strange way.

512
00:42:59,225 --> 00:43:00,424
You can go back to sleep.

513
00:43:01,105 --> 00:43:02,384
I'll go check on your mom.

514
00:43:12,745 --> 00:43:13,665
Mrs. Na.

515
00:43:23,944 --> 00:43:25,105
Here's your apple juice.

516
00:43:25,705 --> 00:43:26,545
Thank you.

517
00:43:27,424 --> 00:43:28,545
I'm sorry.

518
00:43:28,625 --> 00:43:30,585
I woke up late because I was sick.

519
00:43:30,665 --> 00:43:32,705
I almost forgot your apple juice.

520
00:43:34,464 --> 00:43:35,424
That's it?

521
00:43:36,384 --> 00:43:37,585
I was worried.

522
00:43:37,665 --> 00:43:39,705
It's my job to take care of her.

523
00:43:40,265 --> 00:43:41,665
I need to do my best.

524
00:43:43,384 --> 00:43:45,025
Are you going to work today?

525
00:43:45,105 --> 00:43:47,065
I didn't have time to prepare anything.

526
00:43:47,145 --> 00:43:48,225
Can you wait?

527
00:43:49,105 --> 00:43:50,984
I'll help you get it ready in no time.

528
00:44:27,984 --> 00:44:29,025
What brings you

529
00:44:29,105 --> 00:44:30,625
all the way here?

530
00:44:32,464 --> 00:44:34,864
I hear you talked to a doctor in Bangkok.

531
00:44:35,665 --> 00:44:37,225
Are you sending Tarn there?

532
00:44:40,225 --> 00:44:41,585
I've got connections.

533
00:44:45,345 --> 00:44:48,545
I'm aware that the chance
of Tarn waking up is slim to none.

534
00:44:49,625 --> 00:44:51,185
But I want to do my best.

535
00:44:52,705 --> 00:44:54,705
He doesn't deserve any of this.

536
00:44:55,225 --> 00:44:56,745
It's too cruel.

537
00:44:58,225 --> 00:45:00,025
He's unfortunate.

538
00:45:00,864 --> 00:45:03,105
I still stand by what I said.

539
00:45:03,185 --> 00:45:04,944
I agree with you

540
00:45:05,025 --> 00:45:07,785
and I'm willing to cover
all of the expenses

541
00:45:08,625 --> 00:45:10,665
if it will get us out of trouble.

542
00:45:13,185 --> 00:45:14,225
Trouble?

543
00:45:16,585 --> 00:45:19,745
We don't know who attacked your nephew

544
00:45:20,825 --> 00:45:23,185
but people think it's TRD.

545
00:45:25,065 --> 00:45:27,984
Investors are putting
their investments on hold

546
00:45:28,065 --> 00:45:29,424
because it's too risky.

547
00:45:29,505 --> 00:45:31,984
It's starting to upset the executives.

548
00:45:32,585 --> 00:45:34,585
If this project is terminated,

549
00:45:34,665 --> 00:45:37,424
you, the project manager,
might be in trouble.

550
00:45:45,025 --> 00:45:46,625
I didn't mean to cause any trouble.

551
00:45:46,705 --> 00:45:48,625
But you chose to get involved.

552
00:45:50,265 --> 00:45:51,665
Your wife too.

553
00:45:54,185 --> 00:45:56,745
Or they wouldn't have
asked you to give a testimony.

554
00:45:58,105 --> 00:45:59,025
You know?

555
00:46:00,585 --> 00:46:01,785
That's all I know.

556
00:46:03,505 --> 00:46:06,065
I'm not going to meddle
in your family's business.

557
00:46:07,545 --> 00:46:10,265
I hope you can put an end
to this problem soon

558
00:46:10,345 --> 00:46:12,185
without affecting our work.

559
00:46:13,665 --> 00:46:15,345
If you can't,

560
00:46:15,904 --> 00:46:17,145
I'll have to step in.

561
00:46:43,025 --> 00:46:44,424
I thought you went back.

562
00:46:46,065 --> 00:46:48,625
Didn't you want me
to do my job as his aunt?

563
00:46:48,705 --> 00:46:49,864
Here I am.

564
00:46:52,345 --> 00:46:53,384
It looks like

565
00:46:53,464 --> 00:46:55,665
you're worried about him more than I am.

566
00:46:56,265 --> 00:46:58,185
You must be extremely afraid of him dying.

567
00:46:58,785 --> 00:47:01,025
That's why you are here all day.

568
00:47:01,984 --> 00:47:02,864
Why?

569
00:47:03,505 --> 00:47:04,464
Do you feel guilty?

